{"type":"message","id":"5e62d096","parentId":"012561e0","timestamp":"2026-04-14T04:04:00.210Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the key data. Let me extract the important fields:\n\nFrom the 5-min kline for 2026-04-14:\n`[\"2026-04-14\",\"758.33\",\"781.60\",\"784.72\",\"749.58\",\"295626\"]`\n\nWait - the pre-adjusted prices show \"758.33\" as open, \"781.60\" as close, \"784.72\" as high, \"749.58\" as low. But this doesn't seem right for a stock that's around 277. \n\nOh wait - these are actually the pre-adjusted prices after the 10转4送2 dividend adjustment (a \"10转4送2\" means 10 shares become 14 shares with 2 yuan cash per 10 shares). \n\nBut looking at the actual market data from the qt endpoint, the real prices show today's price at 277.77, yesterday's close at 262.14, and an opening price of 269.50. The market data clearly indicates this is a real-time quote, not adjusted data, which makes sense given the pre-market snapshot timing.\n\nLooking at the order book entries that follow, I'm seeing nested bid-ask levels with multiple price points and corresponding volumes on both sides - bids ranging from 277.83 down to 277.68, and asks starting at 277.76 and 277.72. These appear to be the actual order book depths being displayed.\n\nNow I'm examining the extended market statistics that come after - there's timestamp data, percentage changes showing a 5.96% gain, and then OHLCV data where the high and low are clearly marked at 278.88 and 266.39 respectively, with the current price at 277.77.\n\nI'm also seeing additional fields including volume, turnover value in millions, and a PE ratio of 118.17, though the 5.96% change and high-low range align with what I've already identified for the trading data.\n\nLooking at the 5-minute kline data for today showing an open of 758.33 and close of 781.60 - these appear to be pre-adjusted prices that got split through a 10-to-4 conversion, which would explain why the math doesn't align with my current prices of 269.50 and 277.77. The hfq data is likely showing adjusted historical prices that I'm not interpreting correctly.\n\nThe most reliable reference is the real-time quote data showing today's open at 269.50 and the current price around 277.77 as of 12:03 - these are the actual unadjusted prices I should use. I'm trying to pin down the 11:30 closing price by cross-referencing the real-time quote at 12:03 (277.77) with the 5-minute kline data, but the 781.60 figure doesn't align with today's actual price range. Looking at the kline entry format of [date, open, close, high, low, volume], I can see yesterday's data shows a close of 1455.082, but I'm still trying to locate the specific 11:30 snapshot for today. Let me access the minute-level data directly to verify the actual 11:30 close price. The real-time quote at 12:03 shows 277.77, which is already past the morning session close, so I need to rely on the kline data to establish what the 11:30 closing price actually was. I'm realizing the 5-minute kline data for today is showing pre-adjusted prices rather than actual trading prices, which is why 758.33 doesn't align with the market quote of 269.50 at 12:03. I need to query the minute-level data specifically to get the real 11:30 close price, or pull the 5-minute kline directly from the api without the forward-adjustment factor. the minute-level kline data directly. I'm noticing the hfqday array shows prices in the 1400-1700 range, which suggests the data might be pre-adjusted for a stock split. Since the 10转4送2 split hasn't happened yet, these could be legacy prices before the adjustment was applied.\n\nLet me query the actual minute-level data instead.","thinkingSignature":"9dfc2b9f345c78cff0c0ffdf5835e8a2678230da4f103994d12ee3219bf3f7ca"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1lxdqkn6johf_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Get today's 5-min kline without adjustment to find 11:30 close\ncurl -s \"https://web.ifzq.gtimg.cn/appstock/app/fqkline/get?_var=kline_dayfq&param=sh603986,day,,,5,\" 2>/dev/null | iconv -f gbk -t utf-8 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport sys,json,re\ndata = sys.stdin.read()\nm = re.search(r'\\{.*\\}', data)\nif m:\n    d = json.loads(m.group())\n    stock = d['data']['sh603986']\n    print('Keys:', list(stock.keys()))\n    # Try day key\n    if 'day' in stock:\n        print('day (last 3):')\n        for x in stock['day'][-3:]:\n            print(' ', x)\n    if 'fqday' in stock:\n        print('fqday (last 3):')\n        for x in stock['fqday'][-3:]:\n            print(' ', x)\n    if 'qfqday' in stock:\n        print('qfqday (last 3):')\n        for x in stock['qfqday'][-3:]:\n            print(' ', x)\n    if 'hfqday' in stock:\n        print('hfqday (last 3):')\n        for x in stock['hfqday'][-3:]:\n            print(' ', x)\n\""}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1lxdqkn6johf_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Get 5-min kline specifically for today to get 11:30 close\ncurl -s \"https://web.ifzq.gtimg.cn/appstock/app/fqkline/get?_var=kline5min&param=sh603986,5min,,,20,\" 2>/dev/null | iconv -f gbk -t utf-8 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport sys,json,re\ndata = sys.stdin.read()\nprint(data[:4000])\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":4833,"output":1321,"cacheRead":13979,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":20133,"cost":{"input":0.0014498999999999998,"output":0.0015852,"cacheRead":0.0008387399999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00387384}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776139404347,"responseId":"062cef8c33bc4cd097fab603618d5b0c"}}
