{"type":"message","id":"bb22235e","parentId":"f225e3a8","timestamp":"2026-04-14T04:05:08.323Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the hfqday data which includes data for 2026-04-14:\n`[\"2026-04-14\",\"1495.47\",\"1540.86\",\"1546.95\",\"1478.41\",\"295626\",{},\"4.43\",\"811035\",\"\"]`\n\nThis is the forward-adjusted price data (hfq = 后复权). The hfq data shows for today:\n- Open: 1495.47 (hfq adjusted)\n- Close: 1540.86 (hfq adjusted - this should be the 11:30 close in hfq terms)\n\n\n- High: 1546.95 (hfq adjusted)\n- Low: 1478.41 (hfq adjusted)\n- Volume: 295,626 lots\n- Turnover: 811,035 (万元)\n\nBut wait, the current price is 277.77 unadjusted, and I need to verify this makes sense. Yesterday's close was 262.14 unadjusted. If I calculate the adjustment factor using the hfq data for yesterday, the ratio between adjusted and unadjusted prices should give me the factor to convert today's close back to unadjusted terms.\n\nWhen I work through the math, the unadjusted close for today should be around 275.39, but the real-time data shows 277.77 at 12:04, which doesn't match. The problem is that the hfq \"close\" of 1540.86 for today is actually a forward-adjusted price, not the true closing price, so this approach isn't giving me the actual unadjusted close I need. Let me try a different method instead.\n\nLooking at the real-time data more carefully: the open is 269.50, and the current price at 12:04 is 277.77 with a high of 278.88 and low of 266.39. The volume shows 295,626 lots traded between 9:30 and 12:04. Since it's currently lunch break, that current price is technically the last traded price before the market paused. I need to figure out what the actual close was at 11:30.\n\nLet me try querying a different data source to get the intraday 5-minute or 1-minute kline data.","thinkingSignature":"1decb465e0be0b2882fde9cf898318257099885216d6bb2e555d4fdf770b8e3e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wric6dm62z76_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Try getting 1-minute intraday data from Tencent Finance\ncurl -s \"https://web.ifzq.gtimg.cn/appstock/app/fqkline/get?_var=k1md&param=sh603986,m1,,,10,\" 2>/dev/null | iconv -f gbk -t utf-8 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport sys,json,re\ndata = sys.stdin.read()\nm = re.search(r'\\{.*\\}', data)\nif m:\n    d = json.loads(m.group())\n    print(json.dumps(d, ensure_ascii=False)[:3000])\nelse:\n    print(data[:1000])\n\""}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wric6dm62z76_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Try another Tencent API for minute-level intraday data\ncurl -s \"https://gu.qq.com/app/gp/kline/kline?_var=kln&param=sh603986,m1,,,10,\" -H \"Referer: https://gu.qq.com\" 2>/dev/null | iconv -f gbk -t utf-8 2>/dev/null | head -c 2000\necho \"\"\n# Also try the Sina Finance API\ncurl -s \"https://money.finance.sina.com.cn/quotes_service/api/json_v2.php/CN_MarketData.getKLineData?symbol=sh603986&scale=5&ma=no&datalen=10\" 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport sys,json\ndata = sys.stdin.read()\nprint(data[:2000])\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":10044,"output":821,"cacheRead":13979,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":24844,"cost":{"input":0.0030131999999999997,"output":0.0009851999999999999,"cacheRead":0.0008387399999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.004837139999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776139490444,"responseId":"062cefe2ba78b107f6fd728193f34dac"}}
