{"type":"message","id":"b886ce85","parentId":"2df84714","timestamp":"2026-04-14T04:05:22.288Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the 5-minute kline data for today including the 11:30 candle. Let me also get the earlier candles (9:30 and 10:00, 10:05, etc.) to get the full picture.\n\nFrom the data I can see:\n- 11:30 close: 277.770\n- 11:30 high: 277.770\n- 11:30 low: 276.660\n- 11:30 open: 276.800\n\nLet me get the earlier data too.","thinkingSignature":"82a1cff15415ad7b929689aac030be9e8b180c01cd7e0c527847439c35039b69"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_cgxeh6ykmqdx_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Get full day's 5-min data from Sina Finance\ncurl -s \"https://money.finance.sina.com.cn/quotes_service/api/json_v2.php/CN_MarketData.getKLineData?symbol=sh603986&scale=5&ma=no&datalen=60\" 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport sys,json\ndata = sys.stdin.read()\nklines = json.loads(data)\n# Find 9:30 and 11:30 candles\nfor k in klines:\n    t = k['day']\n    if '09:30' in t or '09:35' in t or '09:40' in t or '11:25' in t or '11:30' in t or '09:45' in t or '10:00' in t or '10:05' in t or '10:10' in t:\n        print(f\\\"{t}: O={k['open']} H={k['high']} L={k['low']} C={k['close']} V={k['volume']}\\\")\nprint('...')\nfor k in klines[-5:]:\n    print(f\\\"{k['day']}: O={k['open']} H={k['high']} L={k['low']} C={k['close']} V={k['volume']}\\\")\nprint(f'Total candles: {len(klines)}')\n\""}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_cgxeh6ykmqdx_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Get the 9:30 open candle (first candle of the day)\ncurl -s \"https://money.finance.sina.com.cn/quotes_service/api/json_v2.php/CN_MarketData.getKLineData?symbol=sh603986&scale=5&ma=no&datalen=80\" 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport sys,json\ndata = sys.stdin.read()\nklines = json.loads(data)\n# Print first few candles of today\ntoday_candles = [k for k in klines if k['day'].startswith('2026-04-14')]\nprint(f'Today candles: {len(today_